    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer10232081" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3766841620595280260">First of all, I need to point out that this book is *nothing* like the standard King lineup. Its a refreshing change of pace for his Constant Reader. <br/><br/>Strangely enough, I think Stephen King felt the same way. There&apos;s a passion in the lines of this one that almost makes the words glow on the page.<br/><br/>If I were to recommend a Stephen King book to a &quot;fraidy cat&quot; this would be the one. Its not scary, not even really creepy, although it does have some fairly tense scenes. <br/><br/>You&apos;ll love this little girl by t</span>
  <span id="freeText3766841620595280260" style="display:none">First of all, I need to point out that this book is *nothing* like the standard King lineup. Its a refreshing change of pace for his Constant Reader. <br /><br />Strangely enough, I think Stephen King felt the same way. There's a passion in the lines of this one that almost makes the words glow on the page.<br /><br />If I were to recommend a Stephen King book to a "fraidy cat" this would be the one. Its not scary, not even really creepy, although it does have some fairly tense scenes. <br /><br />You'll love this little girl by the first page, laugh and cry with her through the middle, and cheer when she throws the most important ball of her life.<br /><br />The Girl Who Loved Tom Gordon is a page turner, with a main character you'll not soon forget.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3766841620595280260" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


